<subSubSection lastPageId="47" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="46" pageNumber="47" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="46.[264,1324,1766,1873]" lastBlockId="47.[264,1324,284,1590]" lastPageId="47" lastPageNumber="48" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[264,409,1766,1792]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Description</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[425,488,1766,1792]" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Male</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[504,567,1767,1792]" italics="true" pageId="46" pageNumber="47">Head</emphasis>
. Front with silver white scales, hair wanting; face white pilose, bare medially, silvery white tomentum lateral to antennal base; antenna black; scape and pedicel with white hair; first flagellomere linear, tapering from base to acuminate apex; antennal ratio: 
<number box="[444,461,284,310]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="9.0">9</number>
: 
<number box="[465,483,284,310]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="4.0">4</number>
: 
<number box="[488,522,284,310]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="19.0">19</number>
; oral margin white; gena and upper half of occiput with white hair and scales; ocellar tubercle with long white hair and shorter (inconspicuous) black hair.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[264,1324,284,1590]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis box="[312,396,364,389]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Thorax</emphasis>
. Mesonotum dull black, lateral margin, anterior to wing base cinereous; median longitudinal stripe cinereous, reaching transverse suture; notum with white pile, posterior half medially with shorter black hair, tomentum golden yellow, scales scattered; pleura and legs with white hair and scales, a few golden scales present on femora; halter with stems and knob white; scutellum with white hair and scattered golden yellow scales.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[264,1324,284,1590]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis box="[312,370,564,589]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Wing</emphasis>
. Hyaline; venation normal; crossvein r­m at middle of cell dm; vein m­cu slightly sinuous; basicosta with white hair.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[264,1324,284,1590]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis box="[312,422,644,669]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Abdomen</emphasis>
. Dorsum white pilose, golden yellow tomentose; lateral margin and venter white pilose and tomentose; sternites with posterior margins narrowly pale.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[264,1324,284,1590]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis box="[312,422,724,749]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Genitalia</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[444,536,724,750]" captionStart="FIGURES 46 – 49" captionStartId="43.[264,382,1573,1597]" captionTargetBox="[325,1257,610,1549]" captionTargetId="figure@43.[321,1262,607,1553]" captionTargetPageId="43" captionText="FIGURES 46 – 49. Geron male genitalia. 46, G. niveus Painter; a, lateral view; b, tip of gonocoxa, dorsal view, epiphallus removed. 47, G. notios Hall &amp; Evenhuis, sp. nov.; a, lateral view; b, gonocoxa, dorsal view. 48, G. painteri Hall &amp; Evenhuis, sp. nov.; a, lateral view; b, tip of gonocoxa, ventral view. 49, G. parvidus Painter; a, lateral view; b, gonocoxa, dorsal view, epiphallus and phallic complex removed." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156854/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[505,536,724,750]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="49.0">49</number>
</figureCitation>
) with gonocoxa in ventral view with a single basal depression ridged on either side; in lateral view, gonocoxa, narrowly elongate, with a small rounded protuberance apically; gonostylus normal lateral ramus narrow, coextensive with gonostylus; dorsolateral ramus thickened, slightly curved, rounded apically.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[264,1324,284,1590]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,403,883,909]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Female</emphasis>
. As in male except as follows: 
<emphasis box="[773,836,884,909]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Head</emphasis>
. Eyes half times width of and tomentum, white pedicel at vertex separated more than one and one­half width of ocellar tubercle; front with pale yellow hair tomentum laterally and above antenna; with short black hair; occiput with yellow scales on upper half. 
<emphasis box="[764,848,1004,1029]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Thorax</emphasis>
. Mesonotum with scattered golden yellow tomentum, scutellum and abdominal dorsum with yellow tomentum. 
<emphasis box="[1150,1261,1044,1069]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Genitalia</emphasis>
with posterior projection of tergite VIII black; vaginal furca (
<figureCitation box="[926,1012,1084,1110]" captionStart="FIGURES 13 – 18" captionStartId="7.[264,383,1579,1603]" captionTargetBox="[427,1170,314,1567]" captionTargetId="figure@7.[417,1178,313,1569]" captionTargetPageId="7" captionText="FIGURES 13 – 18. Geron vaginal furcae. 13, G. monticola Hall &amp; Evenhuis, sp. nov. 14, G. nevadensis Hall &amp; Evenhuis, sp. nov. 15, G. nigripes Painter. 16, G. notios Hall &amp; Evenhuis, sp. nov. 17, G. painteri Hall Evenhuis, sp. nov. 18, G. parvidus Painter." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156845/files/figure.png" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
Fig. 
<number box="[982,1012,1084,1110]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="18.0">18</number>
</figureCitation>
) with upper half narrowly V­shaped; lower half with both pieces widely separated, strut broad, flared apically with an inward projection.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="47.[264,1324,284,1590]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,382,1203,1229]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<typeStatus box="[312,382,1203,1229]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Types</typeStatus>
</emphasis>
. 
<typeStatus box="[413,522,1204,1230]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Holotype</typeStatus>
male and allotype (Los Banos, Merced County, California, 
<date box="[264,401,1244,1270]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="1930-07-28">
<number box="[264,295,1244,1270]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="28.0">28</number>
.vii. 
<number box="[337,401,1244,1270]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="1930.0">1930</number>
</date>
, T.F. Winburn, R.H. Painter) in 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" box="[775,860,1244,1270]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">USNM</collectionCode>
(No. 
<date box="[928,1021,1244,1270]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="29-10-14">
<number box="[928,1021,1244,1270]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="101429.0">101429</number>
</date>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="47.[264,1324,284,1590]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,444,1283,1309]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Discussion</emphasis>
. This species is known from the 
<typeStatus box="[851,902,1284,1310]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">type</typeStatus>
locality in northern California and numerous specimens from Deep Canyon in southern California. There are seven specimens in the 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" box="[410,495,1364,1390]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34871" name="Smithsonian Institution, National Museum of Natural History" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">USNM</collectionCode>
that are topotypic but are not labeled as 
<typeStatus box="[982,1098,1364,1390]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">paratypes</typeStatus>
. The single female 
<typeStatus box="[264,365,1404,1430]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">paratype</typeStatus>
from Cajon, California, 
<date box="[657,791,1404,1430]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="1930-07-24">
<number box="[657,688,1404,1430]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="24.0">24</number>
.vii. 
<number box="[729,791,1404,1430]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" value="1930.0">1930</number>
</date>
(T.F. Winburn &amp; R.H. Painter) belongs to 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Bombyliidae" genus="Geron" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripes">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">G. nigripes</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="47" pageNumber="48" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph blockId="47.[264,1324,284,1590]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[312,404,1483,1509]" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Biology</emphasis>
. Immature stages unknown. Adults in Deep Canyon have been collected at flowers of 
<emphasis box="[391,791,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">
<taxonomicName authority="Hyptis" authorityName="Hyptis" box="[391,704,1524,1549]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Loasaceae" genus="Petalonyx" kingdom="Plantae" order="Cornales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="thurberi">Petalonyx thurberi, Hyptis</taxonomicName>
emoryi
</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName box="[856,1024,1524,1549]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Bebbia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Asterales" pageId="47" pageNumber="48" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="juncea">
<emphasis box="[856,1024,1524,1549]" italics="true" pageId="47" pageNumber="48">Bebbia juncea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
